    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><strong>Prerequisite: Proficiency in &amp;reference[Arcana], &amp;reference[History], &amp;reference[Nature], or &amp;reference[Religion].</strong> </em></p><p><em>You've done some studying outside your discipline, and sometimes you just happen to know some very unusual niche information.</em></p><p><strong>No Action Cost</strong> - Self - 1/Short Rest</p><ul><li><p>When you are about to roll an &amp;reference[arcana], &amp;reference[history], &amp;reference[nature], or &amp;reference[religion] check, you can instead roll any one of the other skills from that list.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><em>For example, maybe you use an arcana check instead of a history check for information about an undead king because his son was a powerful mage and you read the son's memoirs. Or maybe you just happen to have heard about the undead king from a friend in wizard school.</em></p>",
